Class ShellCallback

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<java.lang.String>
        • com.topjohnwu.superuser.ShellCallback
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.String>, java.util.Collection<java.lang.String>, java.util.List<java.lang.String>

    public abstract class ShellCallback
extends java.util.AbstractList<java.lang.String>
    An AbstractList only used as an abstract container to call onShellOutput(String) when a new output is added to the list.

    The method onShellOutput(String) will be called in the thread where the ShellCallbackVector is constructed by using Handler. If you need to update the UI, please construct the list in the main thread.
